[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Lab results reviewed. hs-CRP: 5.1 mg/L (elevated, reference less "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "than 3.0). CBC within normal limits. TSH 2.1 (normal). Vitamin D "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "slightly low at 22 ng/mL. IL-6 not ordered this visit. The "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "persistent CRP elevation in the absence of infection or autoimmune "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "disease suggests chronic low-grade inflammation. Discussed with "
