[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "depression phenotype."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Extract Entities from a Clinical Note
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `process_note`. We send each note through Comprehend Medical's DetectEntitiesV2 API to get medical entities with their assertions, attributes, and confidence scores.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def extract_entities_from_note(note: dict) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Send a single clinical note through Comprehend Medical and return
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     structured entity extractions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Comprehend Medical returns entities in several categories:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - MEDICAL_CONDITION: diagnoses, symptoms, signs
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - MEDICATION: drug names with dose/frequency/route attributes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - TEST_TREATMENT_PROCEDURE: labs, tests, procedures
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - ANATOMY: body parts, organ systems
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - TIME_EXPRESSION: temporal references
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Each entity includes Traits (like NEGATION, DIAGNOSIS) and linked
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Attributes (like DOSAGE, DURATION for medications).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note: Dict with keys "note_id", "note_date", "text"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with note metadata and a list of processed entities.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     note_text = note["text"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Comprehend Medical has a 20,000 character limit per call.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Clinical notes rarely exceed this, but in production you'd chunk longer docs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if len(note_text) > 20000:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.warning("Note %s exceeds 20K chars, truncating", note["note_id"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_text = note_text[:20000]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Call DetectEntitiesV2. This is the general-purpose extraction API.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # It returns conditions, medications, tests, anatomy, and temporal expressions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = comprehend_medical.detect_entities_v2(Text=note_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Also call InferRxNorm for normalized medication codes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This gives us RxNorm CUIs so we can match "Effexor" to "venlafaxine".
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rx_response = comprehend_medical.infer_rx_norm(Text=note_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Process entities into a consistent internal format.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     processed = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for entity in response.get("Entities", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Determine assertion status from Traits.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # NEGATION trait means the entity is negated ("denies depression").
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # No NEGATION trait means present/positive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         assertion = "POSITIVE"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         traits = [t["Name"] for t in entity.get("Traits", [])]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if "NEGATION" in traits:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             assertion = "NEGATIVE"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Extract linked attributes (dose, frequency, test values, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         attributes = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for attr in entity.get("Attributes", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             attributes.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "type": attr["Type"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "text": attr["Text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "score": attr["Score"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         processed.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "text": entity["Text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "category": entity["Category"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "type": entity["Type"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "assertion": assertion,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "confidence": entity["Score"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "traits": traits,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "attributes": attributes,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "begin_offset": entity["BeginOffset"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "end_offset": entity["EndOffset"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build a medication normalization lookup from InferRxNorm results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This lets us link brand names to generics later.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rx_lookup = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for rx_entity in rx_response.get("Entities", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if rx_entity.get("RxNormConcepts"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             top_concept = rx_entity["RxNormConcepts"][0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             rx_lookup[rx_entity["Text"].lower()] = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "code": top_concept["Code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "description": top_concept["Description"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "score": top_concept["Score"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "note_id": note["note_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "note_date": note["note_date"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "entities": processed,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "rx_normalization": rx_lookup,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "entity_count": len(processed),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Evaluate Note Against Phenotype Criteria
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `evaluate_against_criteria`. For each criterion in our phenotype definition, we check whether this note's entities provide supporting evidence.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def normalize_medication_name(text: str, rx_lookup: dict) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Normalize a medication mention to its generic name using RxNorm.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Falls back to lowercase text if no normalization is available.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is critical for criterion C2: "sertraline" and "Zoloft" must be
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recognized as the same medication, not counted as two distinct failures.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     lower_text = text.lower().strip()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if lower_text in rx_lookup:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Use the RxNorm normalized description (always generic name)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return rx_lookup[lower_text]["description"].lower()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return lower_text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def text_matches_terms(entity_text: str, target_terms: list) -> bool:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Check if an entity's text matches any of the target terms.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Uses case-insensitive substring matching.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is deliberately permissive. In production you'd add fuzzy matching
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     or embedding-based similarity for terms that vary in spelling.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     lower_text = entity_text.lower().strip()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for term in target_terms:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if term in lower_text or lower_text in term:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             return True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def check_failure_context(entity: dict, note_text: str, failure_indicators: list) -> bool:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Check whether a medication mention appears in a context indicating
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     treatment failure. We look at the surrounding text for failure language.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is a simplified heuristic. A production system would use a trained
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     classifier for treatment outcome assertions, not substring matching.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     But this demonstrates the concept.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Look at a window around the medication mention for failure language.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     start = max(0, entity["begin_offset"] - 200)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     end = min(len(note_text), entity["end_offset"] + 200)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     context_window = note_text[start:end].lower()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for indicator in failure_indicators:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if indicator in context_window:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             return True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def extract_numeric_value(entity: dict) -> float | None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Try to extract a numeric value from a test/lab entity's attributes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Comprehend Medical sometimes returns test values as linked attributes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     If not available from attributes, try to parse from nearby text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for attr in entity.get("attributes", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if attr["type"] == "TEST_VALUE":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Try to parse the numeric part from the value text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             value_text = attr["text"].strip()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Remove common units and comparison operators
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for remove in ["mg/l", "pg/ml", "mm/hr", "mg/dl", "<", ">", "="]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 value_text = value_text.lower().replace(remove, "").strip()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             try:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 return float(value_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             except ValueError:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def evaluate_note_against_criteria(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     extraction_result: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     phenotype_def: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     note_text: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Check which phenotype criteria this note provides evidence for.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For each criterion, we filter the extracted entities to those that:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Match the target category (MEDICAL_CONDITION, MEDICATION, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Match the target terms (condition names, drug names, lab names)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Have the required assertion (POSITIVE, not negated)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. Meet the confidence threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     5. Aren't from an excluded section
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns a list of evidence items, each linking an entity to a criterion.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     evidence_items = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     entities = extraction_result["entities"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rx_lookup = extraction_result["rx_normalization"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for criterion in phenotype_def["criteria"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         criterion_id = criterion["criterion_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         target_categories = criterion["target_categories"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         target_terms = criterion["target_terms"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         required_assertion = criterion["required_assertion"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for entity in entities:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Category filter
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if entity["category"] not in target_categories:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Assertion filter: skip negated mentions when we need positive
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if required_assertion == "POSITIVE" and entity["assertion"] != "POSITIVE":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Confidence filter
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if entity["confidence"] < CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Term matching
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if not text_matches_terms(entity["text"], target_terms):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Criterion-specific logic
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             evidence_item = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "criterion_id": criterion_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "note_id": extraction_result["note_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "note_date": extraction_result["note_date"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "entity_text": entity["text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "assertion": entity["assertion"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "confidence": entity["confidence"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "evidence_type": "NLP_EXTRACTION",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # For treatment failure criterion: check failure context
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if criterion_id == "C2_TREATMENT_FAILURE":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 failure_indicators = criterion.get("failure_indicators", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 if not check_failure_context(entity, note_text, failure_indicators):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     continue  # Medication mentioned but no failure context
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # Normalize the medication name for deduplication
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 evidence_item["normalized_medication"] = normalize_medication_name(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     entity["text"], rx_lookup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # For inflammatory markers: check if value exceeds threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if criterion_id == "C3_INFLAMMATORY_MARKERS":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 numeric_val = extract_numeric_value(entity)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 thresholds = criterion.get("value_thresholds", {})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 entity_lower = entity["text"].lower().strip()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 if entity_lower in thresholds and numeric_val is not None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     if numeric_val < thresholds[entity_lower]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         continue  # Value below threshold, not evidence
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     evidence_item["numeric_value"] = numeric_val
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     evidence_item["threshold"] = thresholds[entity_lower]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             evidence_items.append(evidence_item)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return evidence_items
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Aggregate Evidence Across All Notes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `aggregate_patient_evidence`. After processing all notes, we combine per-note evidence into a patient-level summary for each criterion.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def aggregate_evidence(all_evidence: list, phenotype_def: dict) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Combine evidence from all notes into per-criterion summaries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is where the longitudinal view comes together. A single note might
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     mention one failed medication. Another note mentions a second. Only by
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     aggregating across the full record do we see that the patient meets the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "2 distinct medication failures" threshold.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         all_evidence: Flat list of evidence items from all notes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         phenotype_def: The phenotype definition with threshold requirements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict mapping criterion_id to an aggregation result with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - met: bool (does evidence meet the threshold?)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - confidence: float (average confidence of supporting evidence)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - evidence_count: int
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - supporting_notes: list of note_ids
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - details: criterion-specific details (e.g., distinct medications)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Group evidence by criterion
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     by_criterion = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for item in all_evidence:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cid = item["criterion_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if cid not in by_criterion:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             by_criterion[cid] = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         by_criterion[cid].append(item)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for criterion in phenotype_def["criteria"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cid = criterion["criterion_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         criterion_evidence = by_criterion.get(cid, [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if cid == "C2_TREATMENT_FAILURE":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Special aggregation: count DISTINCT failed medications
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             distinct_meds = set()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for ev in criterion_evidence:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 med_name = ev.get("normalized_medication", ev["entity_text"].lower())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 distinct_meds.add(med_name)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             min_required = criterion.get("min_distinct_medications", 2)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             results[cid] = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "met": len(distinct_meds) >= min_required,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "confidence": (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     sum(e["confidence"] for e in criterion_evidence) / len(criterion_evidence)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     if criterion_evidence else 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "evidence_count": len(criterion_evidence),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "supporting_notes": list(set(e["note_id"] for e in criterion_evidence)),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "details": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "distinct_failed_medications": sorted(distinct_meds),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "required": min_required,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Standard aggregation: count evidence instances
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             min_required = criterion.get("min_evidence_count", 1)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             results[cid] = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "met": len(criterion_evidence) >= min_required,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "confidence": (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     sum(e["confidence"] for e in criterion_evidence) / len(criterion_evidence)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     if criterion_evidence else 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "evidence_count": len(criterion_evidence),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "supporting_notes": list(set(e["note_id"] for e in criterion_evidence)),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "details": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "matched_terms": list(set(e["entity_text"] for e in criterion_evidence)),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Classify the Patient
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `classify_patient`. Apply the phenotype logic to determine whether the patient qualifies: DEFINITE, PROBABLE, EXCLUDED, or INSUFFICIENT_DATA.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def classify_patient(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     criterion_results: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     phenotype_def: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Apply classification logic to produce a final patient-level determination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The logic for this phenotype is straightforward: ALL criteria must be met.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - DEFINITE: all criteria met with average confidence >= 0.85
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - PROBABLE: all criteria met but lower confidence, or partial evidence
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - EXCLUDED: explicit contradictory evidence found
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - INSUFFICIENT_DATA: not enough documentation to determine
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In practice, classification logic can be far more complex (weighted criteria,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     hierarchical logic, time-dependent rules). This example keeps it simple.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: The patient identifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         criterion_results: Output from aggregate_evidence().
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         phenotype_def: The phenotype definition.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Complete classification record with all supporting detail.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     all_criteria_met = True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     has_partial_evidence = False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     min_confidence = 1.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for criterion in phenotype_def["criteria"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cid = criterion["criterion_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         result = criterion_results.get(cid, {"met": False, "evidence_count": 0, "confidence": 0.0})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if not result["met"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             all_criteria_met = False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if result["evidence_count"] > 0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 has_partial_evidence = True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             min_confidence = min(min_confidence, result["confidence"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Determine classification
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if all_criteria_met and min_confidence >= 0.85:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         classification = "DEFINITE"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif all_criteria_met:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         classification = "PROBABLE"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif has_partial_evidence:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         classification = "PROBABLE"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         classification = "INSUFFICIENT_DATA"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build the output record. This is what gets written to S3 and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # becomes the authoritative result for this patient.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     record = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "phenotype_id": phenotype_def["phenotype_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "phenotype_version": phenotype_def["version"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "classification": classification,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "criteria_results": criterion_results,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "processing_timestamp": datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "notes_processed": len(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             set(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 note_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 for cr in criterion_results.values()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 for note_id in cr.get("supporting_notes", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "pipeline_version": "example-1.0",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Full Pipeline: Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the complete flow assembled into a single callable function. This processes one patient's notes through the entire phenotype extraction pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def run_phenotype_extraction(patient_id: str, notes: list, phenotype_def: dict) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the full phenotype extraction pipeline for a single patient.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, this would be orchestrated by Step Functions:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Fan out across Lambda invocations for per-note processing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Accumulate evidence in DynamoDB
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Run aggregation and classification as a final step
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For this example, we process sequentially in-memory.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: Unique patient identifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         notes: List of note dicts with keys: note_id, note_date, text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         phenotype_def: The phenotype definition to evaluate against.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         The final classification record.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"\n{'='*60}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"PHENOTYPE EXTRACTION: {phenotype_def['phenotype_name']}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"Patient: {patient_id}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"Notes to process: {len(notes)}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"{'='*60}\n")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 1 + 2: Process each note and evaluate against criteria
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     all_evidence = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for i, note in enumerate(notes, 1):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print(f"[Step 1-2] Processing note {i}/{len(notes)}: {note['note_id']}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print(f"           Type: {note.get('note_type', 'Unknown')}, Date: {note['note_date']}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Extract entities using Comprehend Medical
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         extraction = extract_entities_from_note(note)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print(f"           Entities extracted: {extraction['entity_count']}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Evaluate entities against phenotype criteria
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         evidence = evaluate_note_against_criteria(extraction, phenotype_def, note["text"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print(f"           Evidence items found: {len(evidence)}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for ev in evidence:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             print(f"             -> {ev['criterion_id']}: '{ev['entity_text']}' "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                   f"(confidence: {ev['confidence']:.2f})")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         all_evidence.extend(evidence)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 3: Aggregate evidence across all notes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"[Step 3] Aggregating evidence across {len(notes)} notes...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     criterion_results = aggregate_evidence(all_evidence, phenotype_def)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for cid, result in criterion_results.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         status = "MET" if result["met"] else "NOT MET"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print(f"         {cid}: {status} "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m               f"(evidence: {result['evidence_count']}, confidence: {result['confidence']:.2f})")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if "details" in result:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             print(f"           Details: {result['details']}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 4: Classify the patient
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("[Step 4] Classifying patient...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     classification = classify_patient(patient_id, criterion_results, phenotype_def)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"         Classification: {classification['classification']}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"         Notes processed: {classification['notes_processed']}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return classification
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Run the pipeline on our synthetic patient
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if __name__ == "__main__":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = run_phenotype_extraction(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id="SYNTH-0042871",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         notes=SYNTHETIC_NOTES,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         phenotype_def=PHENOTYPE_DEFINITION,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("=" * 60)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("FINAL RESULT:")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("=" * 60)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(json.dumps(result, indent=2, default=str))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Storing Evidence in DynamoDB (Production Pattern)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m In the full architecture, evidence accumulates in DynamoDB as notes are processed. Here's how you'd write and query evidence in the production pipeline:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_evidence_item(patient_id: str, evidence_item: dict) -> None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Write a single evidence item to DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The table uses patient_id as partition key and a composite sort key
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     of criterion_id + note_id for efficient per-patient, per-criterion queries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     DynamoDB gotcha: floats must be wrapped in Decimal. boto3's resource layer
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     raises TypeError on raw Python floats.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(EVIDENCE_TABLE_NAME)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     item = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    724[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    725[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "sort_key": f"{evidence_item['criterion_id']}#{evidence_item['note_id']}",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    726[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "criterion_id": evidence_item["criterion_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    727[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "note_id": evidence_item["note_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    728[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "note_date": evidence_item["note_date"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    729[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "entity_text": evidence_item["entity_text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    730[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "assertion": evidence_item["assertion"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "confidence": Decimal(str(round(evidence_item["confidence"], 4))),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "evidence_type": evidence_item["evidence_type"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    733[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "stored_at": datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    734[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    735[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    736[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Add optional fields if present
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    737[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if "normalized_medication" in evidence_item:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    738[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         item["normalized_medication"] = evidence_item["normalized_medication"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    739[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if "numeric_value" in evidence_item:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    740[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         item["numeric_value"] = Decimal(str(evidence_item["numeric_value"]))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    741[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    742[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table.put_item(Item=item)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    743[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    744[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    745[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def query_patient_evidence(patient_id: str) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    746[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    747[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Retrieve all evidence for a patient from DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    748[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    749[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Uses a Query (not Scan) against the partition key for O(1) lookup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    750[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     regardless of table size. This is what the aggregation Lambda calls
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    751[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     after all notes have been processed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    752[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    753[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(EVIDENCE_TABLE_NAME)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    754[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    755[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = table.query(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    756[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         KeyConditionExpression=boto3.dynamodb.conditions.Key("patient_id").eq(patient_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    757[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    758[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    759[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return response.get("Items", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    760[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    761[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    762[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    763[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    764[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Storing Final Results in S3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    765[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    766[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    767[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_classification_result(result: dict) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    768[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    769[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Write the final classification to S3 as a versioned JSON file.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    770[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    771[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The S3 key includes the phenotype ID and version so you can track
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    772[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     how classifications change as the phenotype definition evolves.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    773[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Research reproducibility requires knowing exactly which version of
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    774[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the algorithm produced each classification.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    775[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    776[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns the S3 key where the result was stored.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    777[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    778[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id = result["patient_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    779[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     phenotype_id = result["phenotype_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    780[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     version = result["phenotype_version"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    781[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     timestamp = result["processing_timestamp"].replace(":", "-")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    782[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    783[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     s3_key = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    784[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         f"classifications/{phenotype_id}/v{version}/"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    785[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         f"{patient_id}/{timestamp}.json"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    786[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    787[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    788[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     s3.put_object(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    789[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Bucket=RESULTS_BUCKET,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    790[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Key=s3_key,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    791[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Body=json.dumps(result, indent=2, default=str),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    792[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ContentType="application/json",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    793[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ServerSideEncryption="aws:kms",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    794[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # In production, specify your KMS key ID here:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    795[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # SSEKMSKeyId="arn:aws:kms:us-east-1:123456789:key/your-key-id"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    796[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    797[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    798[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return s3_key
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    799[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    800[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    801[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    802[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    803[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## The Gap Between This and Production
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    804[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    805[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This example demonstrates the shape of a phenotype extraction pipeline. Here's the meaningful distance between this and something you'd actually use for research:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    806[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    807[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Phenotype definition versioning and governance.** In this example, the phenotype definition is a Python dict. In production, it's a versioned artifact in S3 (or a registry service) with formal change control. Changing a criterion definition triggers re-classification of all affected patients and a validation report. You need to know exactly which definition version produced each cohort.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    808[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    809[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Validation infrastructure.** The single most important thing missing here is a validation loop. Before you trust any automated phenotype classification, you need: (1) gold-standard annotations from clinician chart reviewers, (2) a validation sample of 100+ patients, (3) calculated PPV, sensitivity, and specificity, and (4) inter-rater reliability scores showing your annotators agree. Without this, your cohort is noise.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    810[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    811[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Error handling and fault tolerance.** If Comprehend Medical returns an error on one note out of 40, this example crashes. A production pipeline: retries with backoff, logs the failure, continues processing other notes, and marks the patient's classification as "partial" if too many notes failed. Step Functions provides this orchestration natively.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    812[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    813[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Batching and cost control.** This processes notes one at a time. At scale (50,000 patients, 40 notes each = 2 million API calls), you'd batch aggressively, pre-filter patients using structured data queries (only run NLP on patients who pass the ICD-code screen), and use reserved concurrency on Lambda to control costs. The pre-filter step alone can reduce your Comprehend Medical spend by 80-90%.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    814[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    815[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Section detection.** The phenotype definition references "exclude_sections" (like FAMILY_HISTORY), but this example doesn't actually detect which section an entity appears in. Production systems use note section parsers (regex-based or ML-based) that identify standard clinical document sections so you can correctly ignore "Father had depression" when looking for patient depression.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    816[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    817[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Custom models for complex criteria.** "Adequate antidepressant trial" is a nuanced clinical judgment that substring matching handles poorly. A production system trains a custom classifier (hosted on SageMaker) specifically for treatment adequacy assertions. The training data comes from your validation annotations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    818[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    819[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **DynamoDB data types.** Every float that goes into DynamoDB must be wrapped in `Decimal`. This example handles it in the storage functions, but if you add new numeric fields anywhere in the evidence pipeline, remember this constraint. boto3 will raise `TypeError` on raw floats.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    820[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    821[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **IAM least-privilege.** The IAM role running this pipeline should have exactly: `comprehend:DetectEntitiesV2`, `comprehend:InferRxNorm`, `comprehend:InferICD10CM` on all resources; `s3:GetObject` scoped to the notes bucket; `s3:PutObject` scoped to the results bucket; `dynamodb:PutItem` and `dynamodb:Query` scoped to the evidence table. Not `comprehend:*`. Not `s3:*`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    822[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    823[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **VPC and network isolation.** Clinical notes (even de-identified) should never traverse the public internet. Lambda runs in a private VPC with VPC endpoints for Comprehend Medical, S3, and DynamoDB. No internet gateway. No NAT gateway needed for these AWS-to-AWS calls.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    824[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    825[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Reproducibility artifacts.** Research requires complete reproducibility documentation: which pipeline version ran, which phenotype definition version was used, which model versions were active, what the confidence thresholds were, and when the processing occurred. Every run produces a manifest alongside the classifications.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    826[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    827[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Testing.** You need: unit tests for each extraction and matching function (with mocked Comprehend Medical responses), integration tests against Comprehend Medical with known synthetic notes, and end-to-end tests with a reference patient corpus whose correct classifications are known. Never use real patient data in test fixtures.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    828[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    829[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    830[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    831[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Part of the Healthcare AI/ML Cookbook. See [Recipe 8.10](chapter08.10-phenotype-extraction-research) for the full architectural walkthrough, pseudocode, and honest take on where phenotyping gets hard in practice.*
